@node "ultrapinball" "3D Ultra Pinball"

3D Ultra Pinball
Pinball Simulator like Pinball Fantasies on the amiga, but raytraced and you
play with a 3D view. Works ok on:
Amiga 4000, 68030/68882, CyberVision 64,18Mb RAM, 4x NEC CDROM
Kick 3.0/WB 3.1

----------
No problems on:  Amiga 1200/Blizzard1260/24MB RAM/SCSI HD/HD Floppy/
Turbo EVD gfx-driver

@endnode


@node "caliburn" "Crystal Caliburn"
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Name:            Crystal Caliburn

 Genre:           "Flipper" simulator (Pinball)

 Hardware needed: 4MB RAM, mouse, 256color-screenmode

 Software needed: System 6.07

 Description:     Displays the pinball-table on one screen - without
                  scrolling. Good graphics and sounds. Only one
                  table available. Very hard to hold the marble on the
                  table...

 Tested on:       A4000, Cyberstorm040/40MHz, Kick/WB3.0, Cybervision64,
                  A2091-SCSI-Controller, Toshiba XM3801B-SCSI-CD-ROM drive,
                  22MB RAM (10MB assigned to Shapeshifter), MacOS 7.5.5,

 Rating:          Also good playable on A4000/030/25MHz/Cybervision64/16MB
                  Pinball Dreams on Amiga is much much better!!!

 Demo available:  Not known.

 <Tested by: Andreas.Etzrodt@eure.de>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@endnode


